Comments:       Input Driver and support programs for Synaptics touchpads
                Can be used with xf86-input-evdev instead of xf86-input-libinput
                ----
                Even though the evdev driver can handle touchpads well, this
                driver is required if you want to use advanced features like
                multi tapping, scrolling with touchpad, turning the touchpad off
                while typing, etc
